THERE have been strong rains in Limpopo recently and parents must take care
of their children all the time as nearby streams and rivers are full. On Wednesday, 17 February, two teenage boys Thabang Mohale (16) and Maropeng
Maphoto (15) were allegedly swimming with friends when they got swept away and
drowned in Letaba River near Lomondokop village outside Modjadjiskoof. Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe the spokesman for Limpopo police says when they got
notified and a joint search operation was activated consist of the SAPS Water
Wing and other role players from yesterday until today when the two lifeless
bodies were successfully retrieved from the river. "We would like to warn parents to be extra careful and vigilant
whenever they cross the flooded rivers and dams and parents are also warned to
take full care of their children to prevent this type of incidents to
occur," Ngoepe said. Meanwhile, 9-year-old boy Ntsieni Muupo from Pfananani village also drowned
while swimming with friends inside a local dam. 